    {
        "content": "<p>so basic question =&gt; why do i have to put the ID in the URL <strong>AND</strong> in the Body?</p>",
        "id": 153890217,
        "sender_full_name": "Emre Avsar",
        "timestamp": 1495033802
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>short answer: because that's what the spec says: <a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/http.html#update\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/http.html#update\">http://hl7.org/fhir/http.html#update</a></p>",
        "id": 153890359,
        "sender_full_name": "Ben Spencer",
        "timestamp": 1495099270
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Why would you want to update a resource and set its id to null?</p>",
        "id": 153890373,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Mayfield",
        "timestamp": 1495111496
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i'm not interested in setting it to null, i just don't want to repeat my self. either url or body. but if it's written in the spec, maybe it has some reason</p>",
        "id": 153890374,
        "sender_full_name": "Emre Avsar",
        "timestamp": 1495111564
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in an old version of the spec, we did not have this duplication - we did not have .id in the resource. </p>",
        "id": 153890420,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1495131796
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but this is different to most other RESTful interfaces, and caused much discussion and confusion. Eventually, we were persauded that duplication with less confusion is better than non-duplication with more confusion</p>",
        "id": 153890421,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1495131851
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>well it led to more confusion in my case, anyway thanks for the info <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"191316\">@Grahame Grieve</span> </p>",
        "id": 153892425,
        "sender_full_name": "Emre Avsar",
        "timestamp": 1496743901
    }
]